---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import MediaBrowser from '../components/MediaBrowser.astro';

const runModes = [
  {
    id: 'online-service',
    label: 'Online',
    content: `
      <p>The fastest and easiest way to run Thumbrella. Get your <u>free</u> API_KEY
      with one click to register with your Github account.
      <pre><code>curl \\
  -H Authorization: Bearer &lt;API_TOKEN&gt; \\
  https://go.thumbrella.dev/thumb#https://example.com/media.jpg</code></pre>
      <p>This gets you immediate access to the worldwide caching network,
      all the media and document renderers, and access to media from the
      entire internet.</p>
      <p>Like how it's going? Star us on Github to triple your caching and
      processing quotas!</p>
      <p><a href="/docs/aiplatform">Read the AI platform docs</a></p>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'self-hosted',
    label: 'Self Hosted',
    content: `
      <p>Download the standalone executable and run for yourself. Set this up
      for your private libraries and local needs, no internet resources needed.</p>
      <pre><code>thumbrella thumb ./sample.mov --output ./sample.webp
TBR_PORT=8001 thumbrella serve</code></pre>
      <p>Set up your own caching to SQLite with a single configuration argument.</p>
      <p>Advanced renders will require access to external commands and subprocesses.
      Use the internal diagnostics reports to help setting up your environment
      for the optional dependencies.</p>
      <p>Want more control? Grab the Rust source from 
      <a href="http://crates.io">crates.io</a> and build for yourself with <b>cargo</b>.
      <p><a href="/docs/self-hosted">Read the self-hosted docs</a></p>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'ai-platforms',
    label: 'AI Platforms',
    content: `
      <p>Many media tools are already running on AI platforms like 
      <a href="http://replicate.com">Replicate</a> and 
      <a href="http://fal.ai">Fal.ai</a>, and so is Thumbrella.
      Add these lightweight operations alongside your existing computation tools 
      at no extra cost.</p>
      <pre><code>replicate run thumb/rella input=https://example.com/media.mp4</code></pre>
      <p>(These platforms require their own accounts and will bill for processing,
      but Thumbrella will not charge anything for running here)<p>
      <p>Ready to integrate worldwide distributed caching on these platforms?
      Activate a free Thumbrella account with one click using your Github login.
      <p><a href="/docs/aiplatform">Read the AI platform docs</a></p>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'dedicated',
    label: 'Online',
    content: `
      <p>Move beyond the free hosting tiers with greatly increased cache
      storage and concurrency limits.</p>
      <p>With less runtime restrictions your thumbnails will be generated with fewer
      IO operations and improved performance.</p>
      <p>Read the <a href="/pricing">pricing pages</a> for options and details.</p>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'sponsor',
    label: 'Sponsor',
    // follow somewhat https://marijnhaverbeke.nl/fund/
    content: `
      <p>Looking to improve browsing for your own vast media libraries? Building
      a new product that integrates the Thumbrella platform? Becoming a sponsor
      has valuable benefits.</p>
      <p>Sponsors get a Docker-first distrubution enabling all of Thumbrella's
      renderers and media support running out of the box. Get a perpetual
      license that allows a year of upgrades and new releases. The Docker
      image runs completely offline and requires no internet support.</p>
      <p>The sponsored Docker image supports custom caching layers, like writing
      directly to Redis or Postgres</p>.
      <p>This is the cleanest route when you want a containerized deployment, extra standalone capabilities, and a support relationship behind the runtime.</p>
      <p><a href="/docs/sponsor">Read the sponsor docs</a></p>
    `,
  },
];

const freeGroup = runModes.filter((m) => ['online-service', 'self-hosted', 'ai-platforms'].includes(m.id));
const paidGroup = runModes.filter((m) => ['dedicated', 'sponsor'].includes(m.id));
---

<MainLayout
  title="Thumbrella — fast media stack"
  description="Thumbrella is a fast, all-in-one media processing, storage, and delivery toolkit."
>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero__inner">
      <div class="hero__copy">
        <a class="hero__announce" href="/blog/thumbrella-v2">Thumbrella is coming soon →</a>
        <h1>Thumbrella is the <br/><span class="hero__fast" id="hero-typewriter">fast</span><br/>thumbnail platform.</h1>
        <span id="hero-typewriter-words" hidden>fast|open source|online|developer|secure|elegent</span>
        <p class="hero__sub">
          Generate fast and powerful thumbnails online. Check out the flexible
          environments and client libraries you can run for yourself.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero__art">
        <img src="/logotemp.png" alt="Thumbrella logo" class="hero__logo-img" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ RUN MODES -->
  <section class="run-modes-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="run-modes" aria-label="Run Thumbrella">
        <div class="run-modes__tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Run modes">
          <div class="run-modes__group">
            <span class="run-modes__group-label">Run for free</span>
            <div class="run-modes__group-tabs">
              {freeGroup.map((mode) => (
                <button
                  type="button"
                  class:list={['run-modes__tab', mode.id === 'online-service' && 'is-active']}
                  role="tab"
                  aria-selected={mode.id === 'online-service' ? 'true' : 'false'}
                  aria-controls={`${mode.id}-panel`}
                  id={`${mode.id}-tab`}
                  data-panel={`${mode.id}-panel`}
                  tabindex={mode.id === 'online-service' ? '0' : '-1'}
                >
                  {mode.label}
                </button>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="run-modes__group-sep" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="run-modes__group">
            <span class="run-modes__group-label">Powerful paid options</span>
            <div class="run-modes__group-tabs">
              {paidGroup.map((mode) => (
                <button
                  type="button"
                  class="run-modes__tab"
                  role="tab"
                  aria-selected="false"
                  aria-controls={`${mode.id}-panel`}
                  id={`${mode.id}-tab`}
                  data-panel={`${mode.id}-panel`}
                  tabindex="-1"
                >
                  {mode.label}
                </button>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="run-modes__panels">
          {runModes.map((mode, index) => (
            <article
              id={`${mode.id}-panel`}
              class:list={['run-mode-card', index === 0 && 'is-active']}
              role="tabpanel"
              aria-labelledby={`${mode.id}-tab`}
              tabindex={index === 0 ? '0' : '-1'}
              hidden={index !== 0}
            >
              <div class="run-mode-card__content" set:html={mode.content} />
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ DEMO -->
  <section class="hp-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Try it</h2>
      <p class="hp-lede">A sample media library. Thumbnails generate on demand — watch them arrive as the service processes each file.</p>
      <MediaBrowser />
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ FEATURES -->
  <section class="hp-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What makes Thumbrella Great?</h2>
      <p>Generating fast and high quality thumbnails online is
        a challenging problem. To make Thumbrella production ready for your website
        and tools it provides.
      <div class="toolkit-grid">
        <div class="toolkit-card">
          <h3>Hybrid Caching</h3>
          <p>Caches are the most crucial element for speed. Thumbrella makes
            client side caching simple and trouble free. Go even farther with
            server side caches. Our hosted plans use over 300 global regions to
            get thumbnails to your users immediately.
        </div>
        <div class="toolkit-card">
          <h3>Media Types</h3>
          <p>Handle the common formats quickly. Handle the complicated formats efficiently.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Common image formats</li>
            <li>Professional image formats</li>
            <li>Videos</li>
            <li>Vector graphics</li>
            <li>3D Geometry</li>
            <li>Documents</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="toolkit-card">
          <h3>Self Hosted and Open</h3>
          <p>Access the source and build for your own. Prebuilt versions
            are ready to self hosted with no setup or registration needed.
          </p>
          <code class="toolkit-card__cmd">$ TBR_PORT=8001 thumbrella serve</code>
          <a href="http://github.com">Github</a>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


